The article is a statement by President Barack Obama regarding the death of Trayvon Martin. The President acknowledges that the case has evoked strong emotions and asks Americans to respect the call for calm reflection from Trayvon's parents. He also encourages people to consider if they are doing enough to promote compassion and understanding in their own communities and to work towards preventing future tragedies like this. The President emphasizes that it is a collective responsibility and the way to honor Trayvon Martin.